.TH DOTFILES "1" "December 2025" "dotfiles 202305052232-git" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dotfiles \- Legacy wrapper script for dotfiles management and *mgr script execution
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dotfiles
[\fI\,COMMAND\/\fR] [\fI\,OPTIONS\/\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dotfiles
is a legacy wrapper script that provides a unified interface for executing various dotfiles management (*mgr) scripts. It allows users to invoke any of the supported manager scripts (desktopmgr, dfmgr, dockermgr, fontmgr, etc.) through a single command interface.
.PP
The script is now considered obsolete and primarily serves as a compatibility layer for older workflows. Most functionality has been migrated to individual *mgr scripts which can be called directly.
.PP
dotfiles simplifies dotfiles management by providing a single entry point to all manager scripts, allowing quick access to configuration management, package installation, and system setup tools.
