.SH INSTALLED COMMAND
The 'installed' command displays all dotfiles applications managed by this system:
.SS Output Format
.RS
.EX
mgr name:         app name
desktopmgr:       i3
dfmgr:            bash
dfmgr:            vim
fontmgr:          nerd-fonts
.EE
.RE
.SS Color Coding
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
User applications: Blue (color 4) - from ~/.local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/dotfiles
.IP \(bu 2
System applications: Yellow (color 3) - from /usr/local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/dotfiles
.RE
.SS Application Detection
Applications are detected by scanning directory listings:
.RS
.EX
# User directory
ls -A "$HOME/.local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/dotfiles"

# System directory
ls -A "/usr/local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/dotfiles"
.EE
.RE
.SS Filename Format
Application files follow the format: {mgr}-{appname}
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
dfmgr-bash → manager: dfmgr, application: bash
.IP \(bu 2
fontmgr-nerd-fonts → manager: fontmgr, application: nerd-fonts
.IP \(bu 2
desktopmgr-i3 → manager: desktopmgr, application: i3
.RE
