.SH OPERATION
.SS Command Delegation
dotfiles acts as a command dispatcher:
.RS
.IP 1. 3
Parse first argument as command/manager name
.IP 2. 3
Shift arguments to remove command name
.IP 3. 3
Invoke corresponding manager script with remaining arguments
.IP 4. 3
Pass --help flag if no arguments provided
.IP 5. 3
Exit with manager script's exit status
.RE
.SS Default Behavior
When invoked without arguments or with unrecognized command:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Defaults to invoking dfmgr (primary dotfiles manager)
.IP \(bu 2
Passes all arguments to dfmgr
.IP \(bu 2
Shows dfmgr help if no arguments
.RE
.SS Installed Applications Tracking
Applications are tracked by creating files in:
.RS
.EX
# User installations
~/.local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/dotfiles/{mgr}-{appname}

# System installations
/usr/local/share/CasjaysDev/apps/dotfiles/{mgr}-{appname}
.EE
.RE
