.SH TIPS
.SS Direct Manager Invocation
For better performance and clarity, invoke managers directly:
.RS
.EX
# Instead of
dotfiles dfmgr install bash

# Use
dfmgr install bash
.EE
.RE
.SS Querying Installations
Use installed command to audit dotfiles:
.RS
.EX
# See what's installed
dotfiles installed

# Find specific application
dotfiles installed | grep -i bash

# Count by manager
dotfiles installed | awk '{print $1}' | sort | uniq -c
.EE
.RE
.SS Batch Operations
Install multiple applications efficiently:
.RS
.EX
